metadata.description:
Hojae Lee presents a guide on how to run and configure Monty. Walk through a live demo of running an experiment with Monty, as well as an overview of Monty’s modular class structure and ways to build custom configurations.

00:00 Meet Monty 2026: Getting Started With Monty
01:20 Where to Find the Code and Documentation
02:29 Configuration Overview
03:11 Running the Experiment
04:11 Visualization of Monty Running Inference
05:23 Evaluation Statistics
06:16 Overview of Monty Classes
07:06 Example of a Custom Configuration
08:34 Helpful Resources
09:13 Project Showcase

This presentation is part of our December, 2025 community meetup “Meet Monty 2026: Reverse Engineering Intelligence” playlist which you can view here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXpTU6oIscrkM2ZYSohq04cudo1cGGKTb
This two-hour playlist features nine short talks from the Thousand Brains Project team explaining various aspects of the project. Learn about Monty, a new type of AI, based on the principles of the neocortex. 

Get the code: https://github.com/thousandbrainsproject/tbp.monty
Chat with our community: https://thousandbrains.discourse.group
Read the docs: https://thousandbrainsproject.readme.io
Follow us on Bluesky: https://bsky.app/profile/1000brainsproj.bsky.social
